===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} {{term|blue|lang=enm}}, {{term|blewe|lang=enm}}, partly from {{etyl|xno}} {{term|blef|lang=xno}}, {{term|blew|lang=xno}}, from [[w:Old Dutch|Old Low Franconian]] *''blao'' (cf. {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|blauw|lang=nl}}), from {{proto|Germanic|blǣwaz}} (cf. {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|blaw|blāw|lang=ang}}, {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|blau|lang=fy}}, German {{term|blau|lang=de}}, Old Norse {{term|blár|lang=non}}), from {{proto|Indo-European|bʰl(e)h₁uos}} (compare {{etyl|mga|-}} {{term|blá|lang=mga}} 'yellow', {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|flavus|lang=la}} 'id.', {{etyl|lt|-}} {{term|blavas|blãvas|lang=lt}} 'blue'); and partly continuing {{etyl|ang}} {{term|blæwen|blǣwen|lang=ang}} 'blue', from the same {{proto|Germanic}} source. See also [[blae]].

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|blu|er}}

# Having a color [[shade]] close to blue.
# {{informal}} [[depressed|Depressed]], [[melancholic]], [[sad]].
# {{context|entertainment|informal}} [[pornographic|Pornographic]].
# {{US|politics}} Supportive of, run by, or dominated by a poltical party represented by the colour blue. (e.g. The [[Conservatives]], the [[Democrats]])
#: ''I live in a '''blue''' constituency.''
#: ''Congress turned '''blue''' in the mid-term elections.''
# {{astronomy}} Of the higher-frequency region of the part of the [[electromagnetic spectrum]] which is relevant in the specific [[observation]].
# {{context|of [[steak]]}} Extra [[rare]]; left very red and cold.

